I've got a new account set up with my friend Jade. We're using bread as a canvas and seeing how far we can take it by slashing pop culture icons as well as more traditional designs into dough. Follow @thebreadloverssociety for more!

I've not posted for a long time because I've moved house and so many other things but a friend has been encouraging me to bake again recently and these mince pies were something I made for them and their wonderful tea room.

Homemade mince pies with the most delicious mince meat made with vine fruits, cranberries, figs, apples and almonds with the flakiest and lightest sweet shirt crust pastry.

I hope to continue posting pics again in the New Year. My very best wishes to you all xxx

Another shot of my mille-feuille with pistachio creme patissiere, dark chocolate ganache and strawberry compote topped with caramelised meringues, chopped pistachios and strawberry hearts.

Piped using @wiltoncakes no. 12 round and no.32 open star tips.

I made a fun junk food cake for my friend Matt's birthday. It's a three layer chocolate brownie-pretzel-caramel popcorn cake with whipped dark chocolate ganache and chocolate swirls. The first layer has pretzels inside and the second layer has caramel popcorn. 
What's your favourite junk food and do you think it could work in a cake?

Please like and follow me for more 🎂

This cake is made up of alternating layers (4 in total) of chocolate brownie and pink swirled vanilla sponge each topped with Turkish delight and piped rose flavoured Swiss meringue buttercream. All finished with a textured Swiss meringue buttercream in shades of dusky pink. 
I made it for my daughter's birthday.

Please like and follow me for more 🍰

A little something for valentine's day 💚💛💜 Mille-feuille with pistachio creme patissiere, dark chocolate ganache and strawberry compote topped with caramelised meringues, chopped pistachios and strawberry hearts.

I used @wiltoncakes no. 12 round and no.32 open star tips for piping everything (as I know some of you will ask). Are you baking anything special for valentine's day?

Please like and follow me for more 💜

So it was my birthday last week and as it coincides with blood orange season I decided to celebrate the two together. 
I baked a 4 layer vanilla sponge, drenched the layers in lemon syrup, layered them inbetween deep layers of blood orange cream and covered the whole thing with (probably slightly overly) ornately piped meringue and topped it with candied blood orange wedges. I took it into work and we snaffled almost all of it before 11am.

Perfectly imperfect mini mince pies by the fire ready for Father Christmas, a long with a tipple and a carrot for the reindeer. The children are hyped up and psyched up but are at last asleep.

I was saddened recently by the death of Greg Lake, singer of my favourite Christmas song and although the song is invariably seen as a somewhat miserable Christmas tune about either the loss of childhood innocence or the over commercialisation of Christmas at its core there is still a beautiful sentiment and I'm passing on the following lyric to my followers and passersby "I wish you a hopeful Christmas, I wish you a brave new year, All anguish, pain and sadness, Leave your heart and let your road be clear." Merry Christmas you filthy animals.
😄🎄🎁😍 🤗😎

"Oh, bring us some figgy pudding..." A traditional Christmas pudding is a wonderful thing but the ones bought in the shops are dreck. 
We've entered into a cycle of people not liking them because they've only experienced the unpleasant shop bought ones and then making them is never worth the effort because no one likes them. It's a shame.
This particular pudding is packed full of moist sultanas, raisins, figs, apricots, cherries, apples and a lucky silver sixpence. 
Are you a Christmas pudding fan? Have you ever had one?

A tiny panettone (technically a #panettoncino) sitting in my Christmas tree. So light and fruity, this one is topped with an almond and cocoa glaze and sprinkled with sugar pearls. The inside is studded with raisins and candied lemons, oranges and citrons. Check my story for a #crumbshot. 
Sorry I've been so quiet of late; I've not been well. I have however been busy baking Christmas treats that I'll be posting.

A carrot cake with cinnamon buttercream and orange flavoured meringue kisses. I've been making a lot of cakes recently, what should I baketybake next? 
Feel free to tag/share with your friends - please help me hit 10,000! 😍😘

When your friend has been browsing your feed and asks you to make a cake for her five year old sons' birthday and you can't shake the feeling it's really a cake for her. The result is a four tier chocolate brownie cake with milk chocolate ganache swirls and salted caramel drizzle and some milk chocolate footballs. I wrapped the ganache inside the caramel before piping so the ganache swirls are caramel edged. Nom.
A tropical tart! Sablé base covered with coco creme, little domes of pineapple, mango and coconut crémeux and topped with fresh fruit. Goodbye summer! What seasonal treat are you going to miss?
Pink and gold bakewell tart for afternoon tea. A sweet shortcrust pastry case filled with raspberry jam, frangipane and almond flavoured icing.
I decided to not put my usual loaf in its tin. Instead I turned it into a #coburg. I have a story on my page showing some of the steps...follow me for more cool bakes!
A little vanilla cake with dusky pink buttercream made for my nieces. Who else would like a piece?

Apfelkuchen (German apple cake) with cinnamon streusel and salted caramel. This is one of those cakes that looks a bit plain but always tastes amazing.
What's your favourite "plain" cake?

Madeleine should have glorious humps. If they look like body boards rather than cartoon submarines you need to thermo-shock them into going upward.

This one is full of coconut as per @bakrchick 's suggestion.
